The HSE Books Customer Database, held by HSE’s appointed storage and Distribution services provider holds the following information:
There are 19,228 customer records (256 Active and 18,972 closed) documenting orders placed from 1998 to date (31 July 2013).  The orders relate to requests for printed copies of HSE’s guidance portfolio.  These records include data on: Customer Address details;Standard Industry Classification code (SIC) where applicable; Type of business; Number of Employees; Order history; Payment history; Payment type; Credit limit;
This information is provided to HSE for management information purposes.  Sensitive information in relation to payments or bank account details is not shared with HSE and is dealt with under the appropriate financial controls operated by our service provider and the Data Protection Act.
